OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Alec
OL,4,CPenstone
OL,6,FHe said: "I was on the middle watch.
OL,7,F4am to 8am and when I looked through
OL,8,Fthe embarkation space I could see we
OL,9,Fwere anchored and all I could see were
OL,10,Fa mass of ships and houses and trees.
OL,12,F"I thought 'What?' No-one told us what
OL,13,Fwas happening those days. And then one
OL,14,Fof the bunting tossers came down and
OL,15,Fsaid 'I have seen The Needles, we are
OL,16,Foff the Isle of Wight' and that's the
OL,17,Fonly time I knew. And the whole sea
OL,18,Fwas covered with ships.
